text: Arthur McAleenan (October 15, 1894 - May 16, 1920) was an American diver. He competed in three events at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1894 births Category:1920 deaths Category:American male divers Category:Olympic divers of the United States Category:Divers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from New York City
